content: I'm having trouble with Workday. Every time I try to access it, I keep getting an error message that says, 'Error 0x800B0109: A certificate chain processed but terminated in a root certificate which is not trusted.' I've tried clearing my cookies and cache and even restarted my browser, but the issue still persists.
close_notes_ref:
Investigated the reported issue with Workday access and noted the error message: 'Error 0x800B0109: A certificate chain processed but terminated in a root certificate which is not trusted.' 
Checked the browser settings and confirmed that cookies and cache had been cleared as per the customer's attempts. 
Reviewed the certificate settings on the system and identified that the root certificate required for Workday was not trusted. 
Guided the customer through the process of installing the necessary root certificate to establish a trusted connection. 
After the installation, tested access to Workday and confirmed that the error no longer appeared. 
The customer is now able to access Workday without issues. 
Ticket closed as the issue has been resolved and the customer has confirmed satisfaction with the solution.

content: I'm having trouble with my Aruba Networks AirWave software. Every time I try to use it, I keep getting this error message that says 'Error: Uncaught TypeError: Cannot read properties of null (reading 'getAttribute')'. I tried reinstalling the application to fix it, but the problem is still there. Can you help me sort this out?
close_notes_ref:
Investigated the error message 'Error: Uncaught TypeError: Cannot read properties of null (reading 'getAttribute')' encountered in the Aruba Networks AirWave software. 
Checked the software version and confirmed it was up to date. 
Reviewed the application settings and configurations for any discrepancies that could cause the error. 
Found that the issue was related to a specific browser compatibility problem with the AirWave interface. 
Recommended switching to a different browser to access the AirWave software. 
Instructed the customer on clearing the browser cache and cookies before attempting to log in again. 
After these steps, the customer was able to successfully access the AirWave software without encountering the error. 
The issue has been resolved, and the customer expressed satisfaction with the solution. 
Ticket closed.

content: I'm currently having trouble accessing Microsoft Defender for Endpoint on my system. Every time I try to log in, I encounter an error message that states 'java.security.cert.CertificateException: No subject alternative DNS name matching 'api.example.com' found.' I've already attempted restarting both the application and my computer, but the problem still isn't resolved. Can you help me fix this?
close_notes_ref:
Investigated the issue with Microsoft Defender for Endpoint access. 
Noted the error message: 'java.security.cert.CertificateException: No subject alternative DNS name matching 'api.example.com' found.' 
Checked the system's network settings and confirmed that the DNS configuration was correct. 
Reviewed the application version and ensured it was up to date. 
Suggested clearing the Java cache and reattempting the login, but the issue persisted. 
Advised the customer to check for any firewall settings that might be blocking the connection to the API. 
After further troubleshooting, identified that the issue was related to an outdated SSL certificate on the server side. 
Coordinated with the network team to update the SSL certificate for 'api.example.com.' 
Once the certificate was updated, the customer was able to log in successfully without any error messages. 
The customer confirmed that they can now access Microsoft Defender for Endpoint without issues. 
Ticket closed as the problem has been resolved and the customer is satisfied.

content: I've been working with a client facing challenges with their Splunk Core not consistently syncing with Splunk SOAR, resulting in missed automated triggers for some security alerts. After reviewing their system settings, everything appears intact, so we're diving deeper into connectivity logs and network performance to identify any anomalies. It's crucial to rectify this swiftly to maintain their operational efficiency.
close_notes_ref:
Analyzed the client's Splunk Core and SOAR integration to identify sync inconsistencies. 
Reviewed system settings and confirmed they were correctly configured for data synchronization. 
Investigated connectivity logs and network performance metrics to pinpoint any anomalies affecting the sync process. 
Found intermittent network latency that could be contributing to the missed automated triggers for security alerts. 
Recommended adjustments to network configurations to improve stability and reduce latency. 
Provided the client with best practices for monitoring their Splunk environment to ensure ongoing sync reliability. 
The client is now aware of the necessary steps to maintain operational efficiency and prevent future issues. 
Ticket closed as the client is satisfied with the resolution and guidance provided.

content: The customer reports that Google Workspace crashes each time they attempt to save files. They have checked the log files but found no error codes. The issue has been referred to our Software Maintenance Team for further investigation and resolution.
close_notes_ref: Issue observed with Google Workspace crashing whenever files are saved. Investigation started by checking the user's internet connectivity to ensure stable and sufficient bandwidth. Bandwidth and connectivity were found adequate. Next, I cleared the browser cache and cookies to remove any corrupted temporary files. Google Workspace was then tested in an Incognito mode to rule out any extensions or additional browser settings causing the problem. When the issue persisted, I updated the user's browser to the latest version and ensured that all Google Workspace apps were also updated. Finally, I disabled any unnecessary browser extensions and performed a system reboot. After the reboot, Google Workspace operated normally without crashing upon saving files. User confirmed resolution and normal functionality.

content: Every time I try to save my work in Terraform, the application crashes. I've looked into the log files but couldn't find a clear reason for these crashes. Could you please investigate this further?

Verified Terraform installation and version compatibility with the user's system setup. 3. Checked for any recent changes or updates to software or system that might affect Terraform. 4. Ensured sufficient system resources (CPU, memory) for Terraform operations. Resolution: Updated Terraform to the latest stable version, which included fixes for the 'crash on save' issue. The user confirmed that the issue has been resolved following the update.

content: Good day, I've recently integrated Bitbucket with CircleCI to automate our build process. Initially, it worked fine, but now I'm unable to authenticate. I've tried re-entering my account details and even reauthorized the applications, but no luck. Is this a known issue, or am I overlooking something?
close_notes_ref:
Investigated the authentication issue between CircleCI and Bitbucket.  
Checked the integration settings and confirmed that the account details were entered correctly.  
Reauthorized the Bitbucket application within CircleCI to ensure permissions were up to date.  
Reviewed the CircleCI and Bitbucket documentation for any recent changes or known issues regarding authentication.  
Found that there was a temporary outage reported on Bitbucket's end that may have affected the authentication process.  
Informed the customer about the outage and suggested trying the authentication again after some time.  
The customer attempted to authenticate later and confirmed that the issue was resolved.  
Provided recommendations for monitoring the status of integrations in the future to avoid similar issues.  
Ticket closed as the customer is satisfied with the resolution.

content: I am experiencing intermittent issues with mobile access to Citrix ShareFile. On my iPad, I can sometimes access files, but on my Samsung phone, I frequently encounter problems with file upload and download. These issues have been ongoing for several weeks. I've ensured my apps are up to date and my internet connection is stable. This inconsistency is affecting my workflow as I rely heavily on mobile access while traveling.
close_notes_ref:
Investigated the intermittent access issues with Citrix ShareFile on both the iPad and Samsung phone. 
Verified that the mobile app was up to date on both devices, confirming version compatibility. 
Checked the internet connection stability and found it to be consistent. 
Reviewed the app settings and permissions to ensure they were correctly configured for file uploads and downloads. 
Identified that the Samsung phone was experiencing specific issues related to app cache and data storage. 
Cleared the app cache and performed a data refresh on the Samsung device, which resolved the upload and download problems. 
Informed the customer about the importance of regularly clearing app cache to maintain optimal performance. 
The customer confirmed that access to files on both devices is now functioning properly. 
Ticket closed as the issue has been resolved and the customer is satisfied with the outcome.

content: Hello, our team has been encountering significant issues with our system slowing down, and we've traced this back to our Microsoft SQL Server. It appears that some of the queries being run are not only inefficient but are also causing a spike in CPU usage. This has affected our daily operations, as employees are unable to access necessary data promptly. Immediate assistance in identifying and optimizing these queries would be much appreciated to prevent further disruption.
close_notes_ref:
Remoted in to assess the performance issues reported with the Microsoft SQL Server. 
Monitored the server's CPU usage and identified several inefficient queries that were causing significant spikes in resource consumption. 
Analyzed the execution plans for these queries and discovered missing indexes that were contributing to the slowdown. 
Optimized the identified queries by rewriting them for better performance and added the necessary indexes to improve execution times. 
Conducted tests post-optimization to confirm that the system performance had improved and CPU usage was within acceptable limits. 
Informed the team about the changes made and provided recommendations for ongoing query monitoring to prevent future slowdowns. 
The system is now operating smoothly, and the team can access data promptly without disruptions. 
Ticket closed as the issue has been resolved and the customer is satisfied with the outcome.

content: I tried logging in to Jenkins but keep getting 'Invalid Credentials' error even though I'm sure the password is right. Checked if there were any security changes but didn't find anything. Reached out to the Security Team for help.
close_notes_ref: User reported being unable to log in to Jenkins due to 'Invalid Credentials' error despite using the correct password. Steps taken: 1. Verified the username and password entered were correct. 2. Checked the Jenkins server for any failed login attempts or account lockouts. Found that the user's account was temporarily locked due to multiple failed login attempts. 3. Unlocked the user's account and requested them to try again. 4. User was still unable to log in. 5. Looked into the security settings and confirmed no changes or issues. 6. Reset the user's password and provided a temporary one. 7. Guided the user through logging in with the temporary password and setting a new permanent password. User successfully logged in and issue resolved.
